THE grand finale of the Glo Battle of the Year Nigeria dance competition will hold today, April 30, 2022, at the convention centre of the Eko hotel and suites in Lagos. According to information gathered by The Nation, the finale will feature the Bboy, Bgirls, and Breakdance Crew final dance battles.   Davido, Perruzi, Reekado Banks thrill football fans on…     Real Housewives of Lagos: Drama, excitement return to…     Burna Boy speaks on being managed by mom   Already, Glo ambassadors and Nigerian music superstars like Davido, Simi, and Teni Makanaki, have been billed to thrill guests, audience, and judges at the finale. The winner of the Glo Battle of the year 2022 will be getting a mouth-watering sum of N84 million in prize money and an opportunity to represent Nigeria on the global stage for winners at the world’s biggest hip-hop dance show, Battle Of The Year international. For the 2022 edition of the Glo Battle of the year, local and international dance legends such as Gidnasty (USA), Menno (Netherlands), Manuela (Germany), Nigeria’s Poco Lee, Pinky Debbie, Izzy Odigie, Big Flo, Maxbuck, Dunamis, Franc Okwara, JC Jedor, and Poxy (Cameroon), featured as judges throughout the show.